Because even though n is being divided by i, the loop runs up to the initial sqrt(n). Wait, the code is:

int sqrt = (int) Math.sqrt(n);
for (int i = 2; i <= sqrt; i++) {
...
} But after dividing n by i, the sqrt is not updated. So the loop runs up to the initial sqrt of the original n. So that's a point to note.
